Nigerian young star Fikayo Tomori has penned a new four-year contract at the Premier League club Chelsea.
The highly talented centre back has made significant progress over the last 12 months and has been rightly awarded with a new deal.
Tomori made his first team debut against Liverpool, towards the end of last season and will be looking forward to more opportunities like that.
ALSO SEE: Schalke signs Chelsea star
The 18 year old defender was a key part of the Chelsea youth team that clinched the FA Youth cup and the UEFA Youth cup last season.
Tomori was also recognized as the academy’s player of the year after his tremendous
performances and growth in the youth levels.

			
